Guilds no longer have world-based chapters or world boundaries. Influence, merits, upgrades, and bank items have been merged. We've gone ahead and finished building all upgrades in your queue and have refunded duplicates.

—ArenaNet Staff
Unified Guild Chapters

Greetings, Adventurer!

A well seasoned traveler as yourself has probably picked up a lot of very interesting souvenirs along the way. Well now you will find it easier to catalog those findings with a series of new item collection achievements. If you ever feel lost and need more information, come find me in Lion's Arch for further instructions.

-Rednax

Hey, old friend! From what I hear, you've been making quite the impression with the local townsfolk. Hearing how much you've progressed fills me with pride. I urge you to continue your good works in Queensdale and find more people in need. Do that, and you'll make a name for yourself in no time.
—Kella
Kella
You've Come Far

Hero of Shaemoor,

By the Will and Command of Queen Jennah of Kryta, you are hereby formally summoned to attend the royal presence. When you are ready, you are welcome to visit her throne room in Divinity's Reach. Until next we meet, may the Six Gods watch over you in all things.

—Countess Anise

Hey, good work! I'm awfully proud of you.

You've proven that you can stand up and fight for yourself.

You've also proven you can tend your own wounds, even in an unexpected situation, which tells me you're ready to face the challenges of combat.

Now it is time for you to show the courage to walk away from my training grounds and into the unknown.

Shadowy creatures have stolen the luminous orbs that Kella needs to light the island, and she needs them returned to her. I'm sure you can handle it. It'll be a good exercise for you!

—Signe

P.S. I've sent some money along with this letter. Don't forget to <c=@quest>take all</c> of the coins out of the envelope!
Signe
Combat Training: Complete

Not so fast, %str1%! I want you to burn this into your brain: to dodge roll, double-tap your movement keys. Now, drop what you're doing and give me a dodge roll!

Yeah! That's what I'm talkin' about. Never forget it, and even the smoothest of adversaries will fall before you.

—Hroulan
Rolling Success

Thanks for your help, %str1%. Now I can actually walk through my barn without getting a face full of spiderweb. If you're ever looking for something to do, you're welcome at my ranch.

—Tolona Ironrustler
Rancher Tolona Ironrustler
Ranch's Never Looked Better

Hey, thanks for cleaning out the pests in our training area. I haven't seen a single skritt since! I'll make sure the legions hear about your hard work.

—Thegren Topjaw
Thegren Topjaw
Good-bye, Ankle Biters

Thanks to your help at the armory, we'll soon be ready to fire the ol' place up. If you hadn't taken care of those mortar shells and pesky Flame Legion rogues, it might've been forever before we could get back into the arms business.

I know you must be tired from all the fighting at the front, but the way you stepped up and pitched in for the war effort here was commendable.

You're a credit to the legions.

—Crucibis Forgeweld

You work hard, and you work fast. Well done. Now that this mess is all cleaned up, I've got a reward for you. Come see me before moving onto your next task.

Also, don't forget to Take All" of the coins I've attached with this letter.
Legionnaire Lutha Oreseeker
Collect your earnings.

You completed the task I requested of you, and you did it efficiently. Now that the general disarray is somewhat alleviated, I'd like to reward you with some special items I have for sale. Stop by to see me before you move on.

Oh, and don't forget to Take All" of the coins I've attached with this missive.
Krewe Leader Ammi
Receive your reward.

The farmers told me how thankful they are for your help. Their fields have been a lot healthier with less termites around. As a warden, I also give you my thanks. You've done us all a great service.

—Warden Delilah
Warden Delilah
Thanks from the Farmers of Astorea
